## 2026-07-05 â€” Fix MAL token exchange: send client creds in body (drop Basic auth)
- What:
  - internal/repository/oauth/client.go: the token requests (Exchange + Refresh)
    now send `client_id` + `client_secret` as form-body params and no longer set
    an Authorization: Basic header. MyAnimeList's /v1/oauth2/token is unreliable
    with Basic auth and expects credentials in the body; sending both can trip
    "invalid_request". Single, clean body scheme.
  - Non-2xx responses already surface the MAL status + response body in the
    returned error, so a failed exchange shows the real MAL reason in the admin's
    callback Response `message`.
- Why: OAuth authorize succeeded but /v1/connections/callback left the connection
  status="disconnected" â€” the token exchange was failing at MAL (Cause #1 of the
  callback audit). Basic-auth-only requests are rejected by MAL.
- Files: internal/repository/oauth/client.go; internal/repository/oauth/client_test.go (new).
- Tests: added white-box oauth client tests (custom RoundTripper) asserting the
  body carries client_id/client_secret + grant/code/verifier/redirect_uri, that no
  Basic header is sent, that the MAL token URL is hit, and that a non-2xx surfaces
  status+body in the error. `go build/vet` clean; `go test ./...` â†’ 214 pass.
  Coverage: domain 90.0%, service 88.7%, handler 88.2%, d1 82.7%, oauth 88.5%
  (all â‰¥80%).
- Notes: NOT deployed; no wrangler run. Cause #2 (admin token missing the new
  connections.write scope â†’ 401/403 at the gate) is a re-login on the admin side,
  left to the team lead pending the user's callback Response capture.

