## 2026-07-08 â€” Invite-gated self-service registration + pending-review intercept
- What:
  - Public `POST /v1/register` (no bearer token) redeems a single-use invite
    code and creates an admin_user with `email_verified=0` (no usable access).
  - Admin invite management under users.read/write: `POST/GET /v1/invites`,
    `DELETE /v1/invites/{code}` (own path to avoid the `/v1/users/:id` collision).
  - `verifyUser` now rejects unverified accounts (errEmailNotVerified); the login
    UI renders a dedicated "Account under review" intercept page telling the user
    their email is being reviewed by the server owner (instead of a login error).
- Why: user request â€” add register-user feature, invite/allowlist gated, new
  users land email_verified=false with no scopes; plus intercept page for pending
  accounts. Since admin_user has no per-user scope column, "no scopes" is enforced
  by blocking login until an admin verifies (PUT /v1/users/{id}).
