## 2026-07-08 â€” Registration: invite code optional (verified vs pending)
- What: The invite code on self-service register is now optional and controls
  usability. With a valid single-use code the account is created verified
  (email_verified=true) and can sign in immediately; without a code it is
  created unverified and needs admin approval. A supplied-but-invalid code is
  still rejected (403). Applies to both the JSON API (POST /v1/register) and the
  browser signup card; the success card branches (ready-to-sign-in vs awaiting
  approval), and the invite field is labelled optional.
- Why: Allow trusted invited users to self-serve without an admin approval step
  while keeping open (code-less) signups gated.
