## 2026-07-09 â€” Catalog feeds: body pagination + updated_since + limit
- What: Three backward-compatible additions to the per-source catalog feeds
  (GET /v1/sources/:id/{latest,popular,search}).
  1. Response `data` now embeds a `pagination` object
     `{page, perPage, totalCount, hasNext}` â€” the client contract for the
     indexing progress bar / delta sync. `totalCount` = COUNT(*) over the same
     WHERE as the page (a `COUNT(*) OVER()` window column, single query, no extra
     bound params). Legacy top-level `hasNext`/`page` and the `X-Pagination-*`
     headers are kept as-is for backward-compat.
  2. `?updated_since=` filter (Unix epoch seconds OR RFC3339; parsed tolerantly,
     ignored when empty/unparseable) â†’ `AND media.updated_at > ?` on all three
     feeds.
  3. `?limit=` page-size override, clamped to [1,100], default CatalogPageSize
     (30) when absent/invalid, threaded through the service to the repo perPage.
- Why: iOS unified catalog needs %-accurate progress (totalCount), resumable
  incremental sync (updated_since), and tunable page size (limit).
- Files: internal/domain/manga.go (MediaPagination type, MediaPage.Pagination,
  CatalogFilter.Limit/UpdatedSince + PerPage()), internal/domain/pagination.go
  (MaxCatalogPageSize=100), internal/repository/d1/media_repo.go (countWindow
  column on List/Search/Recommend, updated_since clause in filterClauses,
  toMediaPage fills Pagination), internal/handler/response.go (parseCatalogFilter
  reads limit + parseUpdatedSince), internal/handler/media_handler.go (swagger
  @Param for limit/updated_since), internal/service/media_service.go (perPage =
  filter.PerPage()), internal/server/swagger/* (regenerated via make docs);
  tests: domain/manga_test.go, repository/d1/media_repo_query_test.go,
  handler/media_handler_test.go, service/media_service_test.go.
- Tests: go build ./... + go vet ./... clean; go test ./... â†’ 405 pass (was 389).
  Coverage of gated pkgs: domain 100%, service 89.6%, handler 87.5%, d1 82.4%
  (all â‰¥ 80%).
